Description :

1

7

I love the game SABLE by SHEDWORKS. It's probably my favorite game, and a really under-rated gem. This is my tribute to the game, and to the fans of game who, like me, have wanted a little physical model of Sable for their shelves or desks.

The Hakoa top and bottom are my favorite pieces of clothing in the game, so I created this version of Sable dressed in them. I've included two versions, one with the iconic Ibexii mask and one with the Scrapper mask, which is how Sable appears in my playthrough (screenshot attached.)

She's scaled for 28mm gaming, but you can also scale her up to any size that you like.

I really, really hope that we get to see more of SABLE's world in the future. It's really an amazing experience of a game.

Remixed some of my paleolithic people to make some units for Grudge. What is Grudge? Itâ€™s a crunchy little (but still one-sheet) mini-agnostic narrative campaign that Ill Gotten Games is designing for their CRUX: Universal Wargaming rules. It plays in parts as a bloody familial feud and farming sim. Find out more on the IGG Patreon or through DutchMogul here on Thingiverse.

I call these four the Wulfstrael Family, composed of Mother Wulfstrael (who carries a knife and does the butchering.) Old Man Wulfstrael, who dispatches livestock with his trusty hammer, and their two daughters, Hilda and Editha, who hunt game with their bows. The family generally deals in meat and hides, raising cattle, sheep and pigs, but also tanning and preparing pelts and hides for trade.

Just a fan work and a realization of an old dream I had when I was a kid to build a big 'ol army of spacefaring space nuns from 40kya in the future. These sisters love battle, that's for sure!

Seemed like most of the Adepta ladies you can print are resin only, and that just won't do for us old farts tinkering on FDM printers still. This one was printed on an Ender 3!

FDM-4-LIFE!
